16
00:01:01,780 --> 00:01:03,546
In particular, perspective.

17
00:01:03,546 --> 00:01:05,820
Perspective is a broad word.

18
00:01:07,950 --> 00:01:10,087
It includes things like foreshortening.

19
00:01:10,087 --> 00:01:14,776
The fact that three dimensional objects
are projected onto an image plane or

20
00:01:14,776 --> 00:01:16,715
onto our retinal hemisphere.

21
00:01:16,715 --> 00:01:22,710
And that projection creates
foreshortening, so if I look at a unit

22
00:01:22,710 --> 00:01:26,990
cube, when I look at a projection
of the unit cube on an image plane.

23
00:01:26,990 --> 00:01:29,280
Some of the edges
are shorter than the others.

24
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:33,500
The edges in the depth direction
are going to be shorter than the edges

25
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:35,730
in the transverse directions.

26
00:01:35,730 --> 00:01:37,310
And so that's foreshortening,

27
00:01:37,310 --> 00:01:40,910
the effect that this edge is shorter
than this edge in the projection,

28
00:01:40,910 --> 00:01:43,520
even though in the three-dimensional
scene they're the same length.

29
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:50,693
And so lengths in a projection
are not necessarily accurate compared

30
00:01:50,693 --> 00:01:55,778
to the lengths in the real world,
but perceptually we've grown

31
00:01:55,778 --> 00:02:00,505
to understand that these lengths
could be the same length.

32
00:02:00,505 --> 00:02:06,004
And the differences are the result of
the projection onto the image plane.

33
